XI. Conclusion

The Fabric Manager constitutes a critical trust anchor in modern CXL fabrics. We demonstrate that unauthenticated FMAPI operations enable cross-tenant compromise through device reassignment, denial-of-service, and memory reallocation attacks. We propose ZTFM, a zero-trust control-plane architecture that eliminates these vulnerabilities without hardware modification. Experimental evaluation shows complete mitigation of all attack classes with negligible overhead, highlighting the need for authenticated and authorized FM operation in future CXL deployments.
